               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16870223-10-defend74" type="defendantName">
                     Elizabeth 
                     Barly
                  <interp inst="t16870223-10-defend74" type="surname" value="Barly"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870223-10-defend74" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870223-10-defend74" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             of <placeName id="t16870223-10-defloc46">White-Chappel</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16870223-10-defloc46" type="placeName" value="White-Chappel"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16870223-10-defloc46" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870223-10-defend74 t16870223-10-defloc46"></join>, was Tryed likewise upon an Indictment of High-Treason, for that she on the <rs id="t16870223-10-cd47" type="crimeDate">13th. of January</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870223-10-off48 t16870223-10-cd47"></join> last, had <rs id="t16870223-10-off48" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870223-10-off48" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870223-10-off48" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>
               Clipped, Filed, and Deminished, divers pieces of Current Coin, viz. Three Half Crowns Seven Shillings, and one Sixpence of King Charles the First
            </rs>; against whom it appearing upon Tryal, that she had been seen to Rub Clipped Money to bring it smooth, and make it look as if it had not been newly done, as also that it had been her custome, to change away broad Money to Clippers for little Money, at three or four Shillings advantage in the Pound, and that she had been seen to Clip one sixpence; she was found <rs id="t16870223-10-verdict49" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870223-10-verdict49" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs> of the Treason as laid in the Indictment.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16870223-10-punish50" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870223-10-punish50" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870223-10-punish50" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="burning"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870223-10-defend74 t16870223-10-punish50"></join>
               
                     <note>[Death. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
